<p><b>How to stay sane the school of life self-help series?</b> Philippa Perry's 'How to Stay Sane' is a rare gem of a psychological self-help book. Full of practical insights based on sound, up-to-date theory, it is written in a straightforward, sometimes humourous, friendly style that doesn't patronise the reader.</p>
<p><b>How to stay sane book review?</b> It delves into the understanding of our emotions and provides insight into how to manage them effectively, helping readers achieve emotional stability. The book includes a range of relatable examples and exercises to help readers apply the concepts in their own lives, making it highly actionable.</p>
